{
  "stem": "27443.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When they mar-- when the Germans marched into Lodz, we couldn't visualize how bad it would be.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody did.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were right away suffering hunger because nobody worked.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were restricted to-- to our own homes, and we had to stay in lines all night for a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father and I and my older brother, we used to stay all night in the line for a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But unfortunately, after staying a whole night in the line, towards morning, the Germans just arrived and pick out all the Jews-- whoever looked Jew, anything as Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were picked up and beaten up, which my father unfortunately was beaten up many times.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And one of the evenings, one of the nights that I stayed in the line, I witnessed the burning of-- of my temple, my shul, that we used to attend all our lifes.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Our [NON-ENGLISH] shul was in flames.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my father, towards morning, when he was picked out from the line, not getting bread, he went over to the German because my father was very fluent in German language.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He finished his university, his schooling-- he finished in Germany before the war in Berlin, and he got his degree as a mechanical engineer from the University of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So he had experience in the First World War with his classmates, Germans, as well educated people, and he couldn't imagine the torture or the inhuman treatment toward another human being.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he tried to get another piece of bread, going over to the German and begging that he is a former student of Germany.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And speaking in German, it didn't help.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was beaten up and throw in the gutter.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
